{"word":"βύρσα","slug":"βύρσα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βύρσα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>deriv.</a> uncertain\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>the skin stripped off, a hide</i>, <b><a href='S:Batrachomyomachia'>Batr.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>βύρσης ὄζειν</el> to smell <i>of leather</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <i>a drum</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the skin</i> of a live animal, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}